body:
Single bits of bus can be packed back to either slices or to whole bus coz order of signals in input A doesn't matter.
This has no effect to optimisation but is related to slightly cleaner output in backends and in show visualisation. (Extreme low priority)

```
        "_11059_": {
          "hide_name": 1,
          "type": "$reduce_or",
          "parameters": {
            "A_SIGNED": 0,
            "A_WIDTH": 2,
            "Y_WIDTH": 1
          },
          "port_directions": {
            "A": "input",
            "Y": "output"
          },
          "connections": {
            "A" : [["_04194_", 1], ["_04194_", 0]],
            "Y" : ["_04983_"]
          }
        },
```
